personData: Software engineer and Marine Corps veteran passionate about creating amazing user and community experiences, and making an impact in the areas of automation, education, entrepreneurship, writing, and games.

Software Developer with a goal-oriented determination focused on bringing your ideas to the web. I enjoy puzzles and challenges, and I look forward to bringing my varying skillset to your next project.
Formerly self-taught and currently a full stacked developer through Code Fellows intermediate software program

Hi, I am Tim Traylor, an aspiring software developer. I was born in Los Angeles and grew up on a sailboat with my family, so I joined the Navy to see even more of the ocean! After 12 years as a nuclear electrician on submarines and 5 years with King County as an electrical & instrumentation supervisor, I have developed a passion for learning new skills and diving into the details with my team. I am excited to continue my journey in full stack Javascript and see where it leads.
